	   <tr><td colspan=2>There is a new game coming out in the world of MMORPGs in October, and I for one am looking forward to it.  No need to name it, if you are truly interested it can be found on any of a dozen websites.  But what I like is the code to combat farming since most items will be quest related.  In order to actually receive the item, the individual must activate the quest.  So if you kill a MoB which drops it, but don't have quest activated, you don't get it.  In addition, everyone in your group who has the quest activated gets the item at the same time, 1 kill- all have it.  You can't repeat the quest either.  So you loot it once and use, or sell off- but you can't get another unless you buy it from another player. Now that makes sense.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
